  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Smallholders Dairy Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will benefit a total of 300 families in the Bugiri district in Eastern Uganda. Residents of this district are faced with chronic food and income insecurity due mainly to poor agricultural productivity related to poor soil fertility, shortage of land, lack of skills in improved crops and livestock farming, and lack of access to credit. Alcoholism, polygamy, large families, illness and landlessness also contribute to widespread poverty. Fishing on Lake Victoria was once a supplementary source of food and income during lean times; however, it has been in sharp decline due to the rapidly dwindling fish population. Overall, there is inadequate basic social infrastructure in the district, and most of what exists is deficient. For example, although universal primary education is available and is being commended for improving primary school enrollment and benefiting girls and poor children, the quality of education is poor. Families are required to pay for scholastic materials and lunch, which are still not affordable by the majority of families.</narrative>
  </description>
